e\nWater is the most abundant substance on the surface of our planet, covering about 71% of the Earth's surface. However, most of that is saltwater. Only about 2.5% of Earth's water is fresh, and much of that is locked away in glaciers and ice caps, making clean, accessible freshwater a precious and finite resource.\n\n### Summary\nYou can think of water as the **"
